	$1,453,872 and $824,030 for the three months ended June 30, 2016, and 2015 respectively.  The increase is primarily due to
	the acquisition of additional NIBs in September 2015, and adjustments to the cash flow models during the quarter ended June 30,
	2016, which resulted in an increase to the effective interest rate used to recognize income on the NIBs.


	 



